## Design rationale

| Area | Decision |
|---|---|
| **Structure** | Six focused test classes, each mapping to one requirement or boundary domain – makes failures immediately traceable. |
| **Self-contained stubs** | The file runs with `pytest` alone; replace the stub classes with real imports and delete the stubs. |
| **Boundary values** | Exact min/max, one unit below min, one unit above max, and zero are all exercised for both timestamps and numeric quantities. |
| **LOINC validation** | Tests cover `None` code, empty codings list, wrong system URL, LOINC system with empty code value, and a parametrised set of real LOINC codes. |
| **Timezone-awareness** | Naive `datetime` objects are rejected; parametrised offsets (−12 … +12 h) confirm any TZ-aware value is accepted. |
| **Type strictness** | `float` and `int` values for `Quantity.value` are rejected; only `Decimal` is accepted, preventing silent precision loss. |
| **Exception hierarchy** | All domain exceptions inherit from `ValidationError`, so tests can assert at either the specific or the base level. |
